name: Electric Guitars
description: Electric guitars have come to define the very soul of rock, country and countless other genres of popular music. With brands like Gibson, Fender, Rickenbacker, Gretsch and others elevating and perfecting the format in the '50s, electric guitars have evolved over the decades with new designs constantly pushing the instrument into new territory. In the '80s brands like Charvel, Kramer and Ibanez dominated the scene with slick "shredder" guitars. listings.title: Ibanez JEM777V-BK Steve Vai Signature Vine 1989 - Black
listings.description:
Here we have an Ibanez JEM 777V-BK that I am selling because I am trying to thin the herd.

The guitar is in very good condition and set up by me for 9-42 gauge strings.

It has some belt buckle rash on the backside and pick scratches on the pickguard. Also some dings on the edges of the body which are shown in the pictures. Those are just cosmetic and other than that the guitar is in very good shape and plays great. Frets are in very good condition, there are very small divots on the G string area on some frets. Neck is straight and the truss rod works.


I bought this guitar at around 2010 and mostly it has been sitting in its case other than the few times i checked on it and conditioned the fretboard.

The case is not original as far as i know but its an Ibanez RG case nonetheless and fits the guitar well.

listings.model: One 1967 Queen Elizabeth Penny Coin Pick/Plectrum.
listings.title: The Highland Plectrum Co. One 1967 Queen Elizabeth Penny Coin Pick/Plectrum.
listings.description:
One Queen Elizabeth Coin Plectrum.
Made from a genuine 1967 Queen Elizabeth Penny Coin.

Plectrum Dimensions Approximately..
30mm by 27mm by 1.6mm.

Picks made out of metal produce a much brighter sound than plastic. Metal picks made from coins, give players a unique tone as the alloys used in various coinage from around the world vary greatly. Playing guitar with a metal pick gives a unique, rich and bright sound, very different from normal plectrums (Brian May of Queen often plays with a silver sixpence). 
I make the best coin picks!. How can i say this? Take a look at all the other "coin picks" on Reverb and any other online store and compare the attention to detail that shows on my picks versus the other sellers. I take the extra time to make my picks the right way. All the edges and sharp ridges are removed, the edges are beveled properly, and i always complete them in a high polished finish. All of my picks are created one at a time in a small workshop to keep the quality consistent. 
Don't just take my word for it have a look at my feedback.  
SHIPPING FEE
Shipping on two or more plectrums will automatically be combined at check out…….  To keep shipping costs at a reasonable level all orders will be sent by international standard shipping. (Not tracked).  Tracking can be added at additional cost to the buyer. 

I HAVE VARIOUS COIN STYLES AND COIN YEARS AVAILABLE. PLEASE HAVE A LOOK AT MY REVERB SHOP. IF YOU HAVE A SPECIFIC REQUEST DONT HESITATE TO CONTACT ME

Thank you very much for your interest.  Cheers David

listings.title: Gibson Les Paul Modern 2019 - Present - Graphite Top
listings.description: The new Gibson Les Paul™ Modern incorporates many contemporary updates that players have embraced, such as a lighter-weight body and innovative SlimTaper™ neck with an asymmetrical profile. The Modern fingerboard is crafted with genuine ebony and a compound radius for lower and cleaner action. The neck/body joint features the new Modern Contoured Heel for effortless access to the highest frets as well as maximum sustain and stability. Hardware upgrades include Grover® locking Rotomatic® tuners, clear Top Hat knobs, and Burstbucker Pro™ and Burstbucker Pro + pickups. The control assembly features 4 push-pull pots to switch between the Gibson™ humbucker™ and the single coil P-90 sounds, both of which have defined so many genres of music across multiple generations since we invented them, phase switching and pure bypass for functional and versatile sonic variety. The new Gibson Les Paul Modern is here to shape sound for future generations.

Vintage vibe meets modern tone in the Schecter Ultra. The 6-string Ultra features a mahogany body, a 3-piece mahogany neck with a thin "C" profile for high-velocity soloing and an ebony fingerboard for warmth, sustain and effortless playability. Equipped with a Schecter Sunset Strip humbucking bridge pickup and a Schecter Pasadena humbucking neck pickup, the Ultra delivers clear and mellow mids as well as beautiful, warm tones that will cut through any mix. Together, these pickups provide a well-blended yet distinct tone suitable for a variety of musical genres. Additional features include a GraphTech black TUSQ nut, Grover tuners and a TonePros T3BT Tune-O-Matic bridge.

the guitar is used, but nearly like new from 2014...


there is still foil on the back..


the pickguard and the buttons are great yellowed... just as it is available ex works only from the custom shop..

The Squiers are now produced by FENDER in Indonesia and have improved in terms of quality in some points


the sidedots are deeper and you can scallop deeper at this point... the neck feels great.... also the mechanics shine !


perfect for testing a scalloped guitar before buying maybe the Fender

 Yngwie Malmsteen signature model  


Infos to scalloping:


The High-Speed- Shredder Yngwie Malmsteen, even called "Paganini" of Rockguitar, built himself end of 70-ies

a scalloped fretboard to his Strat , as seen on a lute of the 17. century.

Since this time all his most vintageyellow stageguitars are modified in this way to perform 32-tel diagonal runsand arpeggio-cascades ....

even Deep Purple guitarist Ritchie Blackmore played scalloped strats tuned in his own made way...
